<p>Established areas like Brookdale and Mill Creek feature mature homes from the 1970s-1980s with excellent solar potential due to large roof surfaces and fewer shading issues from mature trees. These neighborhoods often see the greatest HVAC energy savings when upgrading from older, less efficient systems. The newer developments in Far South Naperville, including Whispering Hills and Ashwood Park, typically have modern HVAC systems but excellent solar potential with optimal roof angles and minimal shading. HOA considerations may apply in some neighborhoods, though Illinois law generally protects homeowners' rights to install solar panels with reasonable aesthetic guidelines.</p>

